asap.realizer.planunit

Class TimedAbstractPlanUnit

  • java.lang.Object
    • asap.realizer.planunit.TimedAbstractPlanUnit
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TimedPlanUnit
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TimedEventUnit, TimedParameterValueChangeUnit, TimedWaitUnit

    public abstract class TimedAbstractPlanUnit
extends java.lang.Object
implements TimedPlanUnit
    Skeleton implementation of TimedPlanUnit Keeps track of the TimedPlanUnit id information, BMLBlockPeg, feedback listener registration, provides a feedback sending method and keeps track of TimedPlanUnit state.
    Author:
    welberge

      • getPriority

        public int getPriority()
        Description copied from interface: TimedPlanUnit
        Priority of the TimedPlanUnit. It is up to the Player to make execution decisions based upon this value. For example, a Player may decide to drop the TimedPlanUnit with the lowest priority if two TimedPlanUnit conflict. The priority should be interpreted as the current priority of the TimedPlanUnit and might change over time (e.g. the priority of TimedPlanUnits may drop in their subsiding phase).
        Specified by:
        getPriority in interface TimedPlanUnit
